{
  "comment_text": {
    "sn1.26:1.1": "These verses are also at <a href='https://suttacentral.net/sn2.4/en/sujato'>SN 2.4</a>. ",
    "sn1.26:1.3": "Accept variant <i lang='pi' translate='no'>bhavantaṁ</i> in this and similar passages. <i lang='pi' translate='no'>Bhagavantaṁ</i> is hypermetrical. ",
    "sn1.26:2.2": "With this, the Buddha contradicts Yājñavalkya, who posits two additional lights: speech (as when you can make your way in the dark by the sound of another’s voice) and the Self (Bṛhadāraṇyaka Upaniṣad 4.3). "
  },
